Soft Mick is a name used to describe an extravagance in East [[Lancashire]] and [[West Yorkshire]]

The phrase to have ''more <something> than Soft Mick'' means to posess an extravagant quantity of that thing. 

Soft Mick is seemingly used more in [[Accrington]] in conjunction with shoes "More shoes than Soft Mick" Leading some to believe that Soft Mick may have been a Irish shoe peddler working around Accrington, East Lancs, in the early [[20th Century|1900s]]